From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Unipi Technology <dev@unipi.technology>
Date: Mon, 30 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] usb: host: add Rockchip xHCI glue for RK3328

Wire up the Unipi vendor xhci-rockchip driver (provided as a new source
file under drivers/usb/host/ by the board overlay). This driver drives the
DWC3 core directly and configures the UTMI (USB2) PHY by hand, deliberately
leaving the USB3OTG clocks and the (non-existent on RK3328) SuperSpeed PHY
untouched. The generic xhci-dwc3 path enables the USB3OTG clocks through the
clock framework, which interacts badly with the bugged InnoSilicon USB3 PHY
on RK3328 and makes SuperSpeed thumb-drive enumeration marginal.

The xhci-rockchip driver reuses dwc3_set_mode() exported by xhci-dwc3.c,
so it depends on USB_XHCI_DWC3 being built. It provides its own core-init
(rockchip_dwc3_core_init) that soft-resets only the USB2 PHY, never the
bugged USB3 PIPE PHY, so xhci-dwc3's full dwc3_core_init() is not invoked.
The driver only binds nodes whose compatible is "rockchip,rk3328-xhci",
so xhci-dwc3 remains inert when the board DT overrides the dwc3 node's
compatible.

This patch only adds the Kconfig symbol and the Makefile rule; the driver
source itself is added by the Unipi board overlay.

Signed-off-by: Unipi Technology <dev@unipi.technology>
---
 drivers/usb/host/Kconfig  | 9 +++++++++
 drivers/usb/host/Makefile | 1 +
 2 files changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/usb/host/Kconfig b/drivers/usb/host/Kconfig
index 1a2b3c4d5e6f..7a8b9c0d1e2f 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/host/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/usb/host/Kconfig
@@ -33,6 +33,15 @@ config USB_XHCI_DWC3
 	  Say Y or if your system has a Dual Role SuperSpeed
 	  USB controller based on the DesignWare USB3 IP Core.
 
+config USB_XHCI_ROCKCHIP
+	bool "Support for Rockchip on-chip xHCI USB controller"
+	depends on ARCH_ROCKCHIP
+	depends on DM_USB
+	help
+	  Enables support for the on-chip xHCI controller on Rockchip SoCs
+	  using a minimal vendor glue that drives the DWC3 core directly.
+	  Used on RK3328 (Unipi G1) to avoid the bugged InnoSilicon USB3 PHY.
+
 config USB_XHCI_DWC3_OF_SIMPLE
 	bool "DesignWare USB3 DRD Generic OF Simple Glue Layer"
 	depends on DM_USB
diff --git a/drivers/usb/host/Makefile b/drivers/usb/host/Makefile
index 8dad36f9a1b2..c0d1e2f3a4b5 100644
--- a/drivers/usb/host/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/usb/host/Makefile
@@ -46,6 +46,7 @@ obj-$(CONFIG_USB_XHCI_BRCM) += xhci-brcm.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_USB_XHCI_HCD) += xhci.o xhci-mem.o xhci-ring.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_USB_XHCI_DWC3) += xhci-dwc3.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_USB_XHCI_DWC3_OF_SIMPLE) += dwc3-of-simple.o
+obj-$(CONFIG_USB_XHCI_ROCKCHIP) += xhci-rockchip.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_USB_XHCI_EXYNOS) += xhci-exynos5.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_USB_XHCI_FSL) += xhci-fsl.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_USB_XHCI_MTK) += xhci-mtk.o
-- 
